A lot of people spend too much energy in the wrong places when starting a business.

They need to have the perfect website, the perfect product, etc.

Here are some facts:

1. NONE of that matters if don’t have clients and can’t get clients.

2. Most of the positive changes you make to your product or service will come from actually doing the “stuff”(business term) so realistically, all of the changes you’re making before you have any clients is based off of zero data and zero experience.

3. Throw yourself in the fire, make mistakes, fix the mistakes, and repeat. 

The faster you learn the better.
Alot of people come to me for advice and don’t like the answers that they get. Unfortunately there isn’t an easy way to learn without actually learning. #smma #amallbusinesstips

I don’t know if this resonates with anyone else but 👇🏼

1. I started a business because I thought it was an easy way to financial freedom.

2. Invested ALOT just to get started.

3. Didn’t work at first but invested too much to stop - so the motivation to keep going was so that it wasn’t all for nothing.

4. Got better and more passionate about the actual work as opposed to the outcome.

5. Started seeing enough success to keep chasing the reward.

Lesson learned: it’s never going to be as easy as you might think, but that same ignorance is the reason why you start - AND the reason you keep going.

Sometimes “not knowing” works in your favor.
If you want a big reward there will a hefty amount of risk involved. The hardest part is that you have to be willing to bet on yourself OVER and OVER again.

If you’re just starting out.. you can’t expect all your leads to be qualified and ready to go.

-Some leads will be super unqualified 
-Some leads will be super qualified
-Some leads have the potential to be qualified.. but maybe they need a little fore play before they’re actually ready.

Get good at the process

1. Generate leads (in the beginning, ALL leads should be seen as an opportunity)

2. Get good at talking to people and qualifying over the phone 

3. Learn how to sell

4. Here’s a controversial one - UNDERSELL AND OVER-DELIVER

If you’re just starting, you NEED to be okay with doing more for less.
Start at the top of the funnel and work your way down.
Everyone wants to blame the leads. Leads are not always the problem. If you’re running ads to a call booking funnel or an obvious offer, your leads are fine. Just tighten your process.
Provide VALUE.

Starting a business?

1. Enter a growing market
2. Service a growing market

Keep in mind, In order to become an “expert” in any market (failing/ growing), it takes time. Don’t expect overnight success..

Just expect relatively smoother success being in a blue ocean market as opposed to the contrary.
Keep in mind, these “3 things” span over the course of 18 months.
I don’t have a resolution but you’ll probably see some cool shit happen this year 🥂

Got a chance to support some clients at a major event and spend time with quality people. Goal for 2024 -> $3M in Revenue

Wishing everyone the best in 2024
